xt":"The fact that the stone passed spontaneously suggests it might have moved from the kidney to the ureter, but it's not clear if it's still in the system or if it's passed.","dimension":0,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.057023,0.075326,0.085326,0.090107,0.092286,0.093964,0.095985,0.093552,0.090167,0.08633,0.07637,0.063564],"unified_progress":[0.061195,0.079236,0.084293,0.089414,0.093066,0.09523,0.093579,0.094633,0.089616,0.084964,0.074023,0.06075]},{"section":6,"text":"Hexagonal crystals in the urine are a clue.","dimension":11,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.051226,0.079637,0.087861,0.096509,0.095805,0.095476,0.096137,0.089398,0.083869,0.080544,0.075146,0.068394],"unified_progress":[0.049234,0.077092,0.086673,0.094824,0.096583,0.095521,0.094514,0.091618,0.089876,0.083864,0.074526,0.065676]},{"section":7,"text":"I think that hexagonal crystals are a characteristic finding in uric acid stones.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039784,0.064348,0.078962,0.090266,0.098343,0.10163,0.10356,0.10011,0.095275,0.087504,0.074779,0.065443],"unified_progress":[0.036626,0.064308,0.083998,0.094604,0.099146,0.10713,0.10229,0.097668,0.093053,0.088237,0.073516,0.059424]},{"section":8,"text":"Uric acid stones are more common in people with hyperuricemia, often due to conditions like gout or a diet high in purines.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029104,0.057206,0.075078,0.084246,0.096775,0.10298,0.10687,0.10826,0.10477,0.094892,0.076352,0.06347],"unified_progress":[0.041032,0.069782,0.083543,0.092373,0.097531,0.1067,0.10287,0.10119,0.094067,0.087514,0.070339,0.053071]},{"section":9,"text":"The cyanide-nitroprusside test, also known as the Feligee test, is used to detect uric acid in the urine.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032666,0.056956,0.075344,0.086247,0.09866,0.10395,0.10613,0.10423,0.099828,0.090117,0.078219,0.067661],"unified_progress":[0.040103,0.068233,0.084437,0.093077,0.098738,0.1025,0.10062,0.098067,0.094196,0.086706,0.073685,0.059638]},{"section":10,"text":"A positive result means uric acid is present, which supports the diagnosis of uric acid stones.","dimension":7,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036009,0.053846,0.072861,0.084078,0.094235,0.098504,0.10185,0.097868,0.095125,0.091436,0.085937,0.088255],"unified_progress":[0.03932,0.063179,0.078034,0.087286,0.092797,0.097498,0.097637,0.095963,0.093549,0.089428,0.085472,0.079837]},{"section":11,"text":"So putting it together, the presence of hexagonal crystals and a positive cyanide-nitroprusside test points towards uric acid stones.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028022,0.045935,0.05486,0.062109,0.066751,0.071312,0.076445,0.08219,0.090304,0.10581,0.13088,0.18538],"unified_progress":[0.024701,0.042193,0.05226,0.062861,0.067474,0.076637,0.079545,0.088717,0.097156,0.10343,0.13245,0.17257]},{"section":12,"text":"The fact that the stone passed spontaneously might mean it was a kidney stone that moved down the ureter, but the type of stone is more important here.","dimension":0,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.043707,0.049792,0.059448,0.06583,0.07194,0.078599,0.085006,0.0924,0.099827,0.10773,0.11638,0.12934],"unified_progress":[0.044676,0.05602,0.060949,0.067344,0.073323,0.080553,0.084063,0.093089,0.098643,0.10377,0.113,0.12457]},{"section":13,"text":"Therefore, the most likely diagnosis is uric acid nephrolithiasis.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.019184,0.037797,0.050167,0.058576,0.064051,0.06988,0.076973,0.085653,0.095129,0.11351,0.13659,0.19249],"unified_progress":[0.02027,0.039263,0.050739,0.060529,0.06528,0.074204,0.080066,0.089114,0.099302,0.10771,0.13622,0.17731]},{"section":14,"text":"The presence of hexagonal crystals and a positive cyanide-nitroprusside test indicates uric acid stones, which are a type of kidney stone.","dimen